@msharov: Agreed, everything has it's pros and cons. I won't be insulted if this is decided against. 😉
I just find that renaming files is something more often done by user inexperienced with make so I'd like that to be as 'fool-proof' as possible. Somebody adding prerequisites would typically require to adjust the command(s) as well and better knows what (s)he is doing.

edit: An obvious compromise would be using $(word 2, $^) over $(lastword 2, $^) so nothing breaks as long as new prerequisites are added to the end.

